        The facility holds its breath.

        Velvet maintains the distraction—growth surging despite resource depletion—while Remedy keeps deploying chemicals despite being nearly empty, everything committed to this gambit.

        Florence asks, "Runner, status?"

        No response—still nothing. Uh oh.

        Velvet says, "Florence, I'm pulling Velvet's distraction back—I'm completely depleted."

        The distraction stops, and hostile plants immediately recognize it was a feint. They know something happened underground. Bioluminescent signals flash urgently—hostile forces redirect toward Runner.

        Florence shouts, "*Runner, abort — get out of there!*"

        Runner surfaces suddenly, vines torn and withering.

        Runner says, "Can't… reach the command node—too many hostiles—they anticipated the underground approach."

        Florence's platform shifts—frustration, calculation, tactical reassessment happening in real time. Her plan failed.

        The hostile plants are regrouping—they know we tried something and stopped it; now they're coordinating a massive final assault.

        This is bad.

        I ask quietly, "What do we do?"

        Florence is silent, thinking, but I can see in her posture that she doesn't have another plan.

        Holloway says, "We go together."

        Florence says, "What?"

        Holloway says, "Runner couldn't reach the command node alone—so we all go. Collective approach instead of a single assault."

        Florence says uncertainly, "That's not… how do you coordinate everyone underground?"

        Velvet says, "We don't go underground—we bring the command node up."

        Remedy asks, "How?"

        Velvet says, "I grow down—deep, aggressive growth directly toward the command node location—force it to surface to escape."

        Florence processes, "That requires enormous resources—you're depleted."

        Velvet says, "Then Runner helps—we both grow downward together, a combined approach."

        Runner shifts their vines and adds, "I'm injured but I can contribute mass—shared growth."

        Remedy adds, "I provide chemical encouragement—growth accelerants for Velvet and Runner, withering compounds targeting the command node—force it upward through a chemical gradient."

        Florence listens as everyone contributes and a collective solution emerges.

        Florence says slowly, "If you force the command node upward—it surfaces into our defensive perimeter where we can all attack it together."

        Holloway confirms, "Exactly—no single heroic assault, group effort."

        I ask, "Can we actually do this?"

        Florence admits, "Unknown—I've never seen anything like this attempted. But…"

        ¶

        Florence says, "Every voice here contributed to this plan—that has to count for something."

        Scout bounces in hopeful agreement.
      </text>
