        I look around at everyone — Runner torn and leaking, Velvet withered from resource depletion, Remedy chemically empty, Holloway drained, Florence's platform scorched and damaged.

        But we're alive — and we won together — not through Florence's brilliant planning — through collective improvisation.

        Remedy starts, "That was…"

        Holloway finishes, "Effective."

        Velvet adds, "Terrifying."

        Florence says quietly, "Impressive — you all improvised a solution I couldn't have planned — that's… that's real teamwork."

        Nobody responds immediately — the acknowledgment hangs in the air.

        ¶

        Runner says, "We listened to each other."

        Velvet confirms, "And it worked."

        Remedy adds, "Because we trusted each other."

        There it is — the word Florence used earlier: trust — not complete trust — not 'we forgive you for past betrayals' trust — but 'we can work together effectively' trust. Which is a start.

        The facility is wrecked — the hostile plant command node is withering in our central core — everyone is injured and depleted.

        But we're together — actually together.

        Florence wheels backward slightly, giving everyone space — still apart, still not fully included, but less isolated than before.

        Progress — small, fragile, hard-won progress.

        But progress.
